The paper deals with the concept of dimension in simple games, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). It also involves analyzing the growth of dimension, which can be seen as a problem in computational complexity (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The authors use a novel technique, which could be of interest to researchers in machine learning (cs.LG) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
